In the end, everyone has a different way to play the game. Those who like soloing obviously won't get access to higher content than people who like to group just like those who play at night will probably have access to lower content than those who play during prime time hours.  Actually, it's not necessarily lower content, just different content if you find the right mobs to contest. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=graffenlaff>Graffenlaff</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/25/03 1:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Suggestion</span><hr size=1> I apologize in advance to fellow wizards. This thread had almost made it to the next page (and oblivion) ... but, man, after reading it, I have to comment.<br>
<br>
Harvest - quit the game!<br>
<br>
In all the garbled comments I got you have played 243 days are barely level 60 ... er no ... 61 ... er no, died after conning mobs that turned lt blue ... but rezzed back to almost 60 ... wasting time farming for alts but find it stupid to farm for items to sell in the bazaar because no one is on to buy them when you are on (and leaving a trader up while AFK somehow escapes you) ... still hanging out in KC killing greens waiting for VS to spawn which you can't kill because no is online when you play and VS is not soloable .. and on and on and on ... with cyclic inconsistencies to your argument about not being able to get your epic so you want a level 60 spell sheild that will do the skin buff for you.<br>
<br>
I won't even get into the credibility hits you are taking from wizards who actually know you ingame and have commented here.<br>
<br>
Quit the game.<br>
<br>
Cash: on a bad day, where I can only play a few minutes at a time I can sit in elemental heaven to temp flux all the elementals into a nice round package and PBAOE them with 2 shots ... 10% mana at most. Loot the TS items (mercury, lava rocks, etc.) and when I stop playing leave my toon up to sell them. Its not a ton of money all at once, but overtime I have made very considerable chump change from .... very little effort. Now when I have time, there are a few items that sell very fast and for very decent cash and are drops from mobs that take a bit of risk to solo, but not so much that it isn't worth it.<br>
<br>
Exp: there are too many places in the game that you have access to that are still good solo single/quad spots for wizzies to do at level 60 to even discuss. If you have 243  days playing and don't know these areas .. well, that does explain why you are just 60. If you go the extra step and focus on aa xp only, these same places would have you rolling in aa points to build the inherent skills to be an extremely dominant wizzie. At 243 days played, you should know this.<br>
<br>
Reality: frankly, the strongest impression I have of you personally is that you have no friends in game. Instead of building friends you have burned bridges and find yourself at the high end of the game unable to accomplish things ... like epic quests. This of course is just a presumption, based mainly on your complete inability to accept suggestions as such. That said, for your sanity, let me be your &quot;friend for a moment&quot; and finish by saying this:<br>
<br>
You are right. SOE has screwed wizzies over by making them quest for an item that provides a hitpoint buff instead of giving them a new spell at level 60. SOE sucks ... what were they thinking when they added the epic quests to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>EVERQUEST</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->?<br>
